Here is the flow chart for gcd():

Here is the pseduo code for gcd():

if a, b not interger | negative
stop()
if a < b
switch value between a and b

remainder <- a mod b
if (remainder == 0)
  return (b) as gcd
else
  while (remainder != 0) {
    new remainder <- divisor %% remainder
    divisor <- remainder
    remainder <- new remainder
  }
return divisor

gcd <- function(input a, b, c) {
  gcd_betweeb_ab <- gcd(a, b)
  output <- gcd(c, gcd_betweeb_ab)
  output
}

is_prime <- function(x) {
  single_prime <- function(x) {
    if (x is not integer) {stop and exit}
    else if (x less than or equal to 1)
      result = FALSE
    else if (x is 2)
      result = TRUE
    else{
      for (i in sequence(2, x - 1)) {
        if (x is divisible by i)
          result = FALSE break the loop
        else
          result =  TRUE
      }
    }
    output result
  }
  a be empty vector
  for (i in sequence(1, length(x))) {
    prime vector <-
      single_prime(each prime number checked by single_prime() in x)
  }
  prime vector
}

get_factors <- function(x) {
  if (x == 1) {
    output 1
  }
  else {
    for (i in sequence(2, x)) {
      while (x is divisible by i) {
        factor_vector <- i
      }
      j <- j + 1
      x <- x divide by i
      if (after division, x is less than 0)
        break and move to the next i
    }
    prime_factor_position <- which(is_prime(cactor_vector))
    prime_factor <- factor_vector[prime_factor_position]
    prime_factor
    
  }
}
